            <p>Note that "localized daynames" are dependend on the language. They are localized.
This means for one language they are 2 chars, for others 3 chars and for some even 4 chars.</p>

<p>When you need other informations then eighter change the used date constant or change the used information type.</p>

<p>Additionally, please note that this data is used by multiple projects and we are not allowed to change it's content. It's origin is defined from unicode which collect this informations. So when you think there are problems with the content please fill in a issue at unicode so they can fix it.</p>

